### Webhook Registration & Testing Flow

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@contentType = application/json
@webhookUrl = https://webhook.site/your-unique-id-here

### 1. Register a webhook for cv.created events
# Replace @webhookUrl with your webhook.site URL
# @name registerWebhook
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhooks
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "url": "{{webhookUrl}}",
  "event": "cv.created"
}

### 2. Verify webhook was registered (webhook ID: {{registerWebhook.response.body.id}})
# Expected response: webhook created with id

### 3. Now trigger a CV creation to test the webhook
# First, register & login a user (see webhook-flow.http)
# Then create a CV which will emit cv.created event
# The webhook listener will automatically POST the CV to your webhook.url

POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "webhooktest",
  "email": "webhooktest@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 4. Login
# @name webhookLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "webhooktest",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 5. Create CV (this triggers the webhook event)
@webhookToken = {{webhookLogin.response.body.access_token}}

POST {{baseUrl}}/cvs
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{webhookToken}}

{
  "name": "Smith",
  "firstname": "Jane",
  "age": 30,
  "cin": "87654321",
  "job": "DevOps Engineer"
}

### 6. Delete webhook after testing (replace 1 with actual webhook ID)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/1
